<br>
Then I wondered, what if you could buy AA's on the same kind of scale?  How many would do it, and how would it affect the economy?  Go spend your training points + money and buy 1 AA.<br>
<br>
(for example)<br>
1st AA = 1000pp<br>
2nd AA = 2000pp<br>
3rd AA = 3000pp<br>
etc<br>
<br>
How many would you be willing to buy?  At what price would you finally say &quot;no, not worth it&quot;?<br>
<br>
Those people already at 100+ AA's would probably not want to consider it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But perhaps the lower levels would have a chance to catch a few AA's for &quot;training points&quot; and some cash.  You would be limted by number of training points and amount of cash you have.<br>
<br>
Since they like to put these little &quot;moneysinks&quot; into the game anyway, the idea might not be that bizarre.<br>
<br>
